# Mana web app — dev env (Vite reads VITE_* into the client bundle).
# API: the shared EC2 BE via the ALB HTTPS endpoint api.mymana.xyz (ACM wildcard cert;
# TLS terminates at the ALB → forwards to EC2 BE :3000). Same backend the mobile app uses.
# For a LOCAL BE lane, point this at http://localhost:3000 and set
# WEB_ORIGINS=http://localhost:5173 in BE/.env.
#
# NOTE: a browser call to api.mymana.xyz works only once @fastify/cors on the EC2 BE has
# WEB_ORIGINS including the web app's serving origin (e.g. https://web.mymana.xyz, localhost:5173/5174).
# api.mymana.xyz itself is the API host, NOT a CORS origin — it does not go in WEB_ORIGINS.
# LOCAL BE lane via ngrok: web → ngrok → local BE :3000 → local DB. The api client
# sends `ngrok-skip-browser-warning` so the free-ngrok interstitial is bypassed.
# (Direct local was http://localhost:3000; deployed lane is https://api.mymana.xyz.)
VITE_API_URL=https://tristian-folkish-breathlessly.ngrok-free.dev

# Privy DEV app (public — safe in the client bundle). Same app as mobile → same
# user DID. The web origin must be added to Privy dashboard → allowed origins.
VITE_PRIVY_APP_ID=cmoalm0b300vx0djsqojffdy7
# NO client ID on web. @privy-io/react-auth authenticates by App ID + allowed
# origins; passing the mobile/native app client id throws "Invalid nativeAppID".
# (The mobile client id stays in FE/.env only.)
